{"ts":"2026-06-08T23:40:06.860Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-bujg"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Extension teardown: per-deactivate timeout guard so a hanging deactivate() cannot block host shutdown/reload"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"deactivateExtensions runs deactivate hooks concurrently via Promise.all. If one extension's deactivate() never resolves (unresolved promise / infinite await), Promise.all never settles and the host (e.g. the long-running MCP server's teardown finally) hangs indefinitely. Follow-up: race each deactivate() against a bounded timeout (e.g. 5s) so a hanging hook is recorded as a deactivate failure/warning and cannot block the rest or the host. Surfaced by Gemini on PR #150 (loader.ts:1069); deferred from the SDK PR to keep scope focused, but the lifecycle primitive is now in place."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Feature"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":3},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["area:extensions","area:sdk","follow-up","lifecycle","robustness"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-08T23:40:06.860Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-08T23:40:06.860Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-ugqx"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"dd16844eece4e5d1adba23a385ad33066ff710da0f02729e37f871c0e61da4af","message":""}
